    <section class="faq" id="faq">
      <div class="container faq-layout">
        <div class="faq-intro reveal">
          <span class="eyebrow">Questions before setup</span>
          <h2>Know what to expect.</h2>
          <p>For outlet-specific questions, contact the team directly. We can help determine which workflow and plan fit your operation.</p>
          <a class="btn-link" href="https://wa.me/919983721179" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Ask on WhatsApp
            <svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-list reveal">
          <details>
            <summary>Can RestroSuite work with my existing computer or tablet?</summary>
            <p>RestroSuite is web-based and also supports the project’s Android app workflow. Device suitability depends on operating system, browser, printer, network, and the modules you plan to use; these are checked during setup.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What happens after I request registration?</summary>
            <p>Your outlet request is reviewed before activation. The team confirms your business details, required modules, selected plan, and setup needs before issuing workspace access.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Will billing continue if the internet drops?</summary>
            <p>Supported operational workflows are designed with local continuity and later synchronization. Exact offline behavior depends on the active module and device configuration, so it is validated during onboarding.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Does it support GST invoices and multiple payment methods?</summary>
            <p>Yes. The billing workflow supports tax breakdowns and payment categories such as cash, card, and UPI. Your tax configuration remains your business’s responsibility and should be reviewed with your accountant.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Is WhatsApp included in every plan?</summary>
            <p>WhatsApp messaging is an optional gateway capability and is included only where listed or separately agreed. Availability also depends on gateway setup and the applicable WhatsApp service requirements.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Can I change or cancel my plan?</summary>
            <p>Plan changes and cancellation are handled under the applicable service and refund policies. Review the linked policy documents or contact support before subscribing if you need a specific commercial arrangement.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

